jishoData.meaning: sign of the dragon, 7-9AM, fifth sign of Chinese zodiac, shin dragon radical (no. 161)

onyomiExamples.meaning: cinnabar, cinnabarite, cinnabar lacquer, cinnabar lacquerware
celestial bodies, stars, bright star used for timekeeping (e.g. Sirius), Mercury (in ancient Chinese astronomy), Chinese "room" constellation (one of the 28 mansions)
the Sun, the Moon and the stars, the heavenly bodies

kunyomiExamples.meaning: the Dragon (fifth sign of the Chinese zodiac), hour of the Dragon (around 8am, 7-9am, or 8-10am), east-southeast, third month of the lunar calendar
Metal Dragon (17th term of the sexagenary cycle, e.g. 1940, 2000, 2060)
Wood Dragon (41st term of the sexagenary cycle, e.g. 1964, 2024, 2084)
